# Upload button scoped to a document label
# Replace {label} at runtime with first 40 chars of the document type label text
# e.g. ObjReader.getLocator("iNRCISYFUploadBtn").replace("{label}", "Upload Invoice/Receipt")
#
# SCOPING EXPLANATION:
#   Invoice/Receipt and Bank Statement buttons live in bare mat-card-content elements
#   (not inside a mat-card). The outer Status mat-card-content is an ancestor that also
#   matches .//p — causing the locator to match the wrong parent element.
#   Fix: add div[] predicate so we only match mat-card-content where the label <p>
#   is inside a DIRECT div child. This excludes ancestor mat-card-content elements
#   and targets the innermost one that owns both the label and the Upload button.
iNRCISYFUploadBtn                   = //mat-card-content[div[.//p[contains(normalize-space(),'{label}')]] and .//button[.//span[normalize-space()='Upload']]]//button[.//span[normalize-space()='Upload']]
